## Verification

**Core:** (1) Tests passing ≠ program working — always execute. (2) No completion claims without fresh evidence in the current message.

### Execution Verification

After tests pass: CLI → **run it** | API → **call it** | Frontend → **check browser** | Any program → **run it**.

**When:** After tests pass, after refactoring, after changing imports/deps/config, before marking complete.
**Skip for:** Doc-only, test-only, pure internal refactoring, config-only.

### Evidence Before Claims

| Claim | Required Evidence | Insufficient |
|-------|-------------------|-------------|
| "Tests pass" | Fresh run: 0 failures | Previous run, "should pass" |
| "Build succeeds" | Build exit 0 | "Linter passed" |
| "Bug fixed" | Reproducing test passes | "Code changed" |

Before saying "done" or using uncertain language ("should", "probably") — run verification first.
